			  			<HR color=#000000 SIZE=-1>
			  			The final beta test set has come to an end.<br />
<br />
Starting next set, Archspace will be officially out of beta. The reason we are moving out of beta is mostly due to the fact that throught this set we have almost completely stablized the game, and balanced most of the races.<br />
<br />
The new features coming out next set will be:<br />
<br />
Faster/more stable game.<br />
Layout improvements.<br />
New forum (MindBB v2.0).<br />
Server side IRC Client so that everyone can get on irc at any time from any place.<br />
Balanced races.<br />
A new system to prevent quick death and super councils.<br />
Frequent updates: we will post more news to keep player up to date.<br />
New IRC Server: irc.archspace.org port 6666.<br />
Many other small updates that will improve gameplay and stability.<br />
Turns will be a bit longer, 7 minutes instead of 5.<br />
<br />
Since next set will be 99% bug free and balanced, we want to have as many players as possible, so please tell everyone you can about archspace before the set begins.<br />
<br />
The set will begin on friday, December 4th, 2004 at around 16:00 GMT.<br />
<br />
An email will be sent out to all of you a few days before the set begins.<br />
<br />
Thanks,<br />
<br />
- Mindwarper <br />
						<P align=right> </P>
					</TD>
